## A/B Testing for Startups

<div class="my-8 p-6 bg-gradient-to-r from-indigo-50 to-purple-50 border-l-4 border-indigo-500">

### **What to Test First**

**HEADLINE TESTS:**
- Benefit vs feature focus
- Specific vs vague ("10 hours" vs "time")
- Long vs short format
- Question vs statement format

**CTA TESTS:**
- "Start Free" vs "Get Started" vs "Try Now"
- Button color (green vs blue vs orange)
- Button size (large vs medium)
- CTA placement (above fold vs middle vs both)

**SOCIAL PROOF TESTS:**
- Number of users ("Join 500+" vs "Join thousands")
- Metrics ("Save 10 hours" vs "Save time")
- Testimonials (long vs short, with vs without photo)
- Logos (color vs grayscale, number shown)

**TESTING BEST PRACTICES:**
- Test one variable at a time
- Minimum 100 visitors per variant
- Statistical significance: 95% confidence
- Test for 1-2 weeks minimum
- Document results and learnings

